        <briefdescription>
<para>Solve an equation with assumption-based domain filtering. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Calls the existing <ref refid="dc/d25/classSymbolicExpr_1a8e2b693429c55311a664ed0306bc9b2e" kindref="member">SymbolicExpr::solve()</ref> to compute all solutions, then applies domain filtering based on the variable&apos;s declared domain in the <ref refid="de/dc6/classlamina_1_1AssumptionContext" kindref="compound">AssumptionContext</ref>. Solutions that violate the domain constraint are excluded.</para>
<para>Domain filtering rules:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Real: exclude solutions containing sqrt(-1) or non-real numeric values</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>PositiveInt: exclude non-integer or &lt;= 0 solutions</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>NonNegative (Natural): exclude solutions evaluating to &lt; 0</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>equation</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The equation to solve (equal to zero, or <ref refid="d7/d58/classRelationalNode" kindref="compound">RelationalNode</ref>) </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>variable</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The variable name to solve for </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>ctx</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Optional assumption context; if nullptr, all solutions returned unfiltered </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>Filtered solutions preserving original order </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
